commentText:
Rule that runs the test inside a worker looper thread. This rule is responsible of creating a temp directory containing a Realm instance then deleting it, once the test finishes.

All Realms used in a method method annotated with {@code @RunTestInLooperThread } should use {@link RunInLooperThread#createConfiguration()} and friends to create their configurations. Failing to do so can result in the test failing because the Realm could not be deleted (this class and {@link TestRealmConfigurationFactory} do not agree in which order to delete the open Realms).
